1. Definitions
----------------------------------------------------------------------
1.1 "You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under
    this License.
1.2 "Permitted User" means any of the following, acting in good faith:
    (a) an individual clinician, supervisor, behavior analyst,
        paraprofessional, educator, researcher, student, learner,
        parent, caregiver, or self-advocate;
    (b) a school, clinic, agency, university, research group, or
        healthcare provider, whether for-profit or non-profit, using
        the Software internally to deliver services to the people they
        serve;
    (c) a 501(c)(3) or equivalent non-profit organization, or a
        government or public-sector body, using the Software to advance
        its mission.
1.3 "Permitted Purpose" means using, running, studying, modifying,
    and distributing the Software for any of the following:
    (a) direct delivery of clinical, educational, therapeutic,
        supervisory, assessment, or research services to identified
        learners, clients, students, or research participants;
    (b) personal learning, academic study, or non-commercial research;
    (c) internal tooling that supports the activities above, including
        training staff and collaborating with other Permitted Users;
    (d) publishing academic or clinical work that references or
        demonstrates the Software, with attribution.
    Being compensated for your own professional services that happen to
    make use of the Software is Permitted Purpose. Receiving grant
    funding for non-commercial research or public-benefit work is
    Permitted Purpose.
1.4 "Commercial Use" means any use that is NOT Permitted Purpose,
    including but not limited to:
    (a) selling, sublicensing, renting, or leasing the Software or any
        derivative work;
    (b) offering the Software or any derivative work as a hosted,
        managed, or software-as-a-service product to third parties for
        a fee, subscription, or other consideration;
    (c) incorporating the Software or any derivative work into a
        product, service, platform, or bundle that is itself sold,
        licensed, or monetized (including by advertising, data resale,
        or paywall);
    (d) using the Software to train, fine-tune, or evaluate a machine
        learning model that is itself commercially distributed or
        offered as a paid service;
    (e) any use whose primary purpose is to generate revenue from the
        Software itself or access to it, rather than from the services
        delivered by a Permitted User to the people they serve.
